Types of Verdicts

Procedural Decisions (Formal)

-   Case ends without answering guilt question

-   Examples: Wrong court, invalid summons, defendant died, suspension
    of prosecution

-   Case may potentially continue later (not always final)

Substantive Decisions

-   Court answers guilt question

-   **Conviction OR Acquittal**

-   **IMPORTANT: Acquittal ‚â† proven innocent**

```{=html}
<!-- -->
```
-   Just means: insufficient evidence OR legal requirements not met

-   Person must be treated as innocent (presumption of innocence)

-   Example: Marco Borsato case (acquitted but conduct may have been
    immoral)

Sanctions

Penalties

-   **Aimed at punishment for general prevention**

-   Examples:

```{=html}
<!-- -->
```
-   Imprisonment (most serious)

-   Detention (lighter form of imprisonment)

-   Community service / unpaid work

-   Fines

-   Accessory penalties: Deprivation of rights (voting, professional
    rights)

